mao 's last dancer is a 2009 australian film based on professional dancer li &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; 's autobiography of the same name . li &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; is portrayed by birmingham royal ballet principal dancer chi cao ( simplified chinese : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ; traditional chinese : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ; pinyin : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) , australian ballet dancer &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; guo ( chinese : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ; pinyin : &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) and huang wen bin . the film also stars bruce greenwood , kyle maclachlan , joan chen , wang &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and amanda &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; . the film premiered on 13 september 2009 , at the toronto international film festival . general release in australia and new zealand began on 1 october 2009 . it began screening in the united states on 33 screens in august 2010 .